-- ADP Says Companies in U.S. Added 188,000 Workers in June
-- B y   L o r r a i n e   W o e l l e r t
-- 2013-07-03T12:15:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-03/adp-says-companies-in-u-s-added-188-000-workers-in-june.html
Companies in the U.S. boosted employment by 188,000 workers in June, figures from the Roseland, New Jersey-based ADP Research Institute showed today.  The median forecast of 38 economists surveyed by Bloomberg called for an advance of 160,000. Estimates ranged from gains of 100,000 to 196,000.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lorraine Woellert in Washington at  lwoellert@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Chris Wellisz at  cwellisz@bloomberg.net  